          {
            "commit": "5745b7f231b5a45cc7109c84530e20788cbc9373",
            "subject": "LU-8998 utils: enlarge default inode size"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-04-22 23:46:32.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-05 10:17:05.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-8050 osp: not use obdo::o_lcookie for non-onwire RPC data",
        "message": "LU-8050 osp: not use obdo::o_lcookie for non-onwire RPC data\n\nOriginally, obdo::o_lcookie is for destroy with unlink cookie from\nMDS, it is obsolete in 2.8. And then, it is reused by the OSP to\navoid RAM allocations. But now, we needs more fields in the obdo\nstructure to transfer more information from client to OST. The\nobdo::o_lcookie is good candidate. So this patch adjust OSP\nlogic to NOT use such field for non-onwire RPC data usage.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2bff0dce6f00f330657097a9ae9f775396e090cb\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/24876\nReviewed-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
